---
import GameLayout from "../../../layouts/GameLayout.astro";
import Hero from "../../../components/starsavior/Hero.astro";
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<GameLayout
  title="Full Scale Offensive | Chaos Zero"
  description="Full Scale Offensive is a new 6-week cyclical game mode in Chaos Zero Nightmare featuring 3 past Great Rift bosses."
  game="chaoszero"
>
  <Hero
    title="Full Scale Offensive"
    summary="A new cyclical game mode launching in the Death Note pre-season. Form 3 teams to tackle 3 past Great Rift bosses across 6-week seasons."
  />

  <section class="container stack">
    <div class="panel" style="padding: 1.4rem;">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">New Game Mode</p>
          <h2>What is Full Scale Offensive?</h2>
        </div>
      </div>
      <article class="prose">
        <p>
          Full Scale Offensive is a brand-new game mode introduced in the Death Note pre-season.
          Unlike the current Great Rift (which uses cumulative damage scoring), FSO uses a
          <strong>score-based system</strong> where you form 3 separate teams — one for each boss.
        </p>
        <p>
          Each season runs for <strong>6 weeks</strong> and features <strong>3 past Great Rift bosses</strong>.
          You'll use 9 combatants total (3 per team), and each boss has unique bonus mechanics
          you can exploit for extra points.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>

    <div class="panel" style="padding: 1.4rem;">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Key Features</p>
          <h2>How it works</h2>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card-grid">
        <article class="content-card">
          <h3>3 Teams, 3 Bosses</h3>
          <p>
            Form one team per boss. Each team uses 3 combatants, for a total of 9 per run.
            No overlap restrictions — build your best roster for each boss individually.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="content-card">
          <h3>Score-Based Scoring</h3>
          <p>
            Unlike Great Rift's cumulative damage model, FSO uses a point system.
            Each boss has bonus mechanics that reward specific strategies for extra points.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="content-card">
          <h3>6-Week Seasons</h3>
          <p>
            Each FSO season runs for 6 weeks. Bosses rotate between seasons,
            featuring past Great Rift bosses that have already been cleared.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="content-card">
          <h3>Save Data Carryover</h3>
          <p>
            Preseason save data carries into the new season. Old season save data
            will also become usable in Great Rift (future update). Every deck you build
            remains permanently meaningful.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="panel" style="padding: 1.4rem;">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Persona Cards</p>
          <h2>Season 3 Persona Card System</h2>
        </div>
      </div>
      <article class="prose">
        <p>
          Launching alongside Season 3 (April 29, 2026), the Persona Card system adds
          a new progression layer to Full Scale Offensive:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Each combatant gets <strong>one special Persona Card</strong> through engravings</li>
          <li>Cards grow stronger with enhancement effects from bets and exploration</li>
          <li>Engraved equipment is found at waypoints and unidentified areas</li>
          <li>The pre-season lets you preview Persona Cards and carry over save data</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          This system makes every deck you build permanently meaningful — your investment
          in a combatant's Persona Card carries forward across seasons.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>

    <div class="panel" style="padding: 1.4rem;">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Release Timeline</p>
          <h2>Important dates</h2>
        </div>
      </div>

      <table class="event-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Date</th>
            <th>Event</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>April 8, 2026</strong></td>
            <td>Partner system overhaul goes live — partner stats now fully apply to memory fragment percentages, enhanced growth impact, boosted passive stats</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>April 29, 2026</strong></td>
            <td>Season 3 / Half Anniversary — Full Scale Offensive launches with Persona Card system</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="panel" style="padding: 1.4rem;">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Balance Changes</p>
          <h2>Combat adjustments</h2>
        </div>
      </div>
      <article class="prose">
        <p>
          Alongside the new mode, several balance changes are coming:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Yuki</strong> — Another buff incoming (ego manifestation effects adjusted)</li>
          <li><strong>Underperforming combatants</strong> — Usability improvements across the roster</li>
          <li><strong>General roster buffs</strong> — Similar to previous balance passes, expect broader adjustments</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Source: <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZcPmYT8bJc8" target="_blank" rel="noopener">WG: CZN — "CRAZY PATCH INCOMING"</a>
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</GameLayout>

<style>
  .event-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .event-table th,
  .event-table td {
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    text-align: left;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
  }

  .event-table th {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: var(--text-soft);
  }

  .event-table tbody tr:hover {
    background: var(--surface-3);
  }
</style>
